<h2>HVAC Systems for Baton Rouge</h2>
<p>Baton Rouge's hot-humid climate demands robust, efficient HVAC systems capable of handling extreme heat while managing high humidity levels year-round. The ideal HVAC system for this climate should feature a minimum SEER rating of 16-18, with higher ratings providing greater efficiency and comfort. Central air conditioning systems with variable-speed compressors work exceptionally well, as they can adjust cooling output to match demand while maintaining consistent humidity control. Heat pumps are particularly effective in Baton Rouge, providing efficient cooling in summer and adequate heating during mild winters, though backup heat strips may be necessary for occasional cold snaps.</p>

<p>Proper sizing is critical for Baton Rouge HVAC systems, as oversized units will short-cycle and fail to adequately dehumidify, while undersized systems will struggle during peak summer conditions. For the average 1,880 square foot home, a 3-4 ton system typically provides appropriate capacity. Additional considerations include high-quality air filtration to handle humidity-related mold concerns, programmable thermostats to optimize efficiency during varying occupancy, and proper ductwork design with adequate insulation to prevent condensation issues common in humid climates. Regular maintenance is essential, with bi-annual service recommended to ensure peak performance in the demanding Louisiana environment.</p>

