<p>Baton Rouge residents have access to several attractive incentives for solar panel installations. The federal solar Investment Tax Credit (ITC) provides a 30% credit on the total system cost through 2032, then decreases to 26% in 2033 and 22% in 2034. Louisiana offers additional state-level support through the Solar Energy Systems Tax Credit, providing up to \$12,500 in state tax credits for residential installations. This credit equals 50% of the first \$25,000 of system costs, making Louisiana one of the most solar-friendly states in the nation.</p>

<p>Entergy Louisiana participates in net metering programs, allowing solar customers to receive credit for excess electricity fed back into the grid at retail rates. Additionally, solar installations may qualify for property tax exemptions in East Baton Rouge Parish, ensuring that adding solar panels won't increase property tax assessments. For HVAC upgrades, federal tax credits are available for high-efficiency heat pumps and other qualifying equipment, while Entergy offers rebates for ENERGY STAR certified systems. Local utility rebates can range from \$200-\$800 depending on system efficiency ratings and may include additional incentives for smart thermostats and ductwork improvements.</p>

