<p>Baton Rouge's diverse neighborhoods each present unique considerations for solar and HVAC installations. In the historic Garden District and Beauregard Town, older homes with mature tree canopy may require careful solar panel positioning and HVAC system upgrades to accommodate aging electrical systems and limited attic space. The Mid City and Spanish Town areas feature a mix of renovation projects and established homes, often benefiting significantly from combined solar and HVAC upgrades that can transform energy efficiency.</p>

<p>Newer developments like The Lakes, Southdowns, and areas around Burbank Drive typically have more suitable roof orientations for solar panels and modern electrical systems that easily accommodate solar integration. These neighborhoods often feature larger homes that benefit from 8-10kW solar systems paired with zoned HVAC systems. In university areas near LSU, smaller homes and rental properties may be ideal for 4-6kW systems with high-efficiency mini-split HVAC systems. Suburban neighborhoods like Prairieville and areas along Bluebonnet Boulevard offer excellent solar potential with minimal shading and newer construction standards that facilitate both solar and HVAC installations.</p>

